Severity: Critical
Status: Escalated to Tier 2
Attack Technique: Social Engineering


1. Executive Summary

  On February 26, at 03:40AM (PST), a SIEM alert was triggered involving a successfully delivered phishing email to internal user dylan@letsdefend.io, 
  IP 172.16.17.216, promoting a free Windows update. The sender's domain (windows-update.site) tied to IP 132.232.40.201, was unfamiliar to any known legitimate Windows domain.
  After analysis of the sender's domain on VirusTotal, Lumma Stealer infostealer malware was confirmed as the payload. Log analysis confirmed an outbound connection 
  made from 172.16.17.216 (Dylan) to 132.232.40.201 (windows-update.site) 14 hours after the phishing email was recieved, confirming the payload was interacted with by our internal user. Immediate containment of 
  the affected endpoint was employed. Further log analysis confirmed no other internal user recieved or interacted with the malicious payload. Due to the unauthorized
  access of an internal endpoint, escalation to Tier 2 was rendered necessary for further imapct assessment. 


